Considering FIN in a narrow gap, the weak field region, E < Ems [explicitly given in Eq. 7)] can be determined by the condition hc > hgap. In that region, the free energy within the gap is increasing with h making embryos unstable. On the other hand, under higher fields, E > Es [also, explicitly given in Eq. 7)], the barrier is at shorter distance than hc, and yet, the energy F(hgap, rmin) is positive. Therefore, for the field strengths in the interval,7\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
