It follows from the above that while the nucleation of unconstrained CF is possible for the field of any strength (with exponentially field dependent nucleation times), the confined CFs require the field strength E > Ems and the corresponding voltages U > Ums = Emshgap. Similarly, stable CFs can nucleate when U > Us = Eshgap. It follows from Eq. (7) that both Us and Ums are independent of hgap and \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
