The case of very thin dielectrics requires additional comments when the electron transport is ballistic violating the assumption of power generation inside the structure. That assumption underlies the term proportional to σE2 in Eq. (19); it was adopted in all the preceding modeling work30–35. The switching processes of interest take place under voltages of ~1 V, which means that electrons dissipate the energy of ~1 eV (between the electrode quasi-Fermi levels). For the case of ballistic transport, it will be injected in the opposite electrode as the electron kinetic energy with the relaxation length \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
